performed_via_github_app.description:
Amazon Q Developer is a generative AI assistant that enables you to automate code changes and legacy code transformation, all from a GitHub issue. After completing its code changes, Amazon Q Developer generates a pull request for your review. Start with 500 invocations per month of Amazon Q Developer‚Äôs feature development and code review capabilities and 10,000 lines of Java transformations per month. Increase your usage at any time by registering your Amazon Q Developer app installation with your AWS account.

# Feature development

Amazon Q Developer allows you to generate code directly from natural language prompts. You can build new features, debug, refine algorithms by describing your requests and letting Amazon Q Developer perform the tasks. It can help to save time, reduce errors, and improve efficiency with code generation that evolves with your project.

# Code transformation

Amazon Q Developer transforms outdated codebases into scalable, efficient, and maintainable systems. You can update your technology stack, enhance performance, and ensure future compatibility while preserving the core functionality of your existing code. With Amazon Q Developer, you can avoid technical debt and build your applications for long-term implications.

# Code review

With Amazon Q Developer, you can automate code reviews within GitHub. When Amazon Q Developer performs a code review, it analyzes your pull requests, provides feedback on code quality, potential issues, and security concerns. Amazon Q Developer then provides suggestions based on the code review.


# Getting started

1. Select the GitHub repositories that can use Amazon Q Developer and complete the authorization process.
2. Get started using Amazon Q Developer in an issue by adding labels for feature development or code transformation, or by creating a new pull request for code review.

pull_request.title: Refactor: Disable automatic deblurring and make it manual
pull_request.body:
The automatic deblurring functionality has been removed to meet the user's request. Previously, the extension applied the deblur effect automatically when loading the likes page or detecting new likes.

- Removed the `observarMudancasURL` and `configurarObservadorDOM` functions.
- Simplified the `inicializar` function to only set up manual triggers (on-page button and popup message listener).

Now, the deblurring will only occur when the user explicitly clicks the extension button or the floating button on the page.

pull_request.title: feat: Add smart splitting, parallel downloads, and bug fixes
pull_request.body:
This commit introduces several major features and bug fixes to improve the bot's functionality and stability.

Features:
- **Smart Video Splitting:** Implements an intelligent video splitter that uses `ffmpeg` to create parts that are under Telegram's file size limit without re-encoding. Includes a rich UI for split file uploads.
- **Parallel Telegram Downloader:** Adds a high-speed parallel downloader for large files from Telegram, based on the rapidStream method, to significantly improve download speeds.

Bug Fixes:
- **ValueError in video processing:** Fixes a crash caused by an inconsistent return signature in the `process_video` function.
- **Message Flood:** Adds a safeguard to prevent `MESSAGE_NOT_MODIFIED` errors by checking if the status message content has changed before editing.
- **NameError in telegram_download:** Fixes a crash caused by a missing import of the `Config` object.

SonarQube Cloud (formerly SonarCloud) is a SaaS code analysis tool designed to detect coding issues in 30+ languages, frameworks, and IaC platforms. Your code is checked against an extensive set of rules that cover many attributes of code, such as maintainability, reliability, and security issues, on each merge/pull request.

For those requiring US-based hosting, [SonarQube Cloud US](https://sonarqube.us/) offers the perfect alternative. If you need data residency outside the US or within the EU, [SonarQube Cloud](https://sonarcloud.io/) with this GitHub app is the ideal solution.

SonarQube Cloud integrates seamlessly into your GitHub workflow and provides clear guidance for resolving any code quality and security issues detected. The majority of popular languages can be analyzed automatically; no configuration is required!

With [SonarQube Cloud](https://sonarcloud.io/github), you get:

-   Fast, precise static analysis and feedback on your code
    
-   Support for popular languages, frameworks, and IaC tools
    
-   Free analysis for open-source projects and private projects up to max 50k LoC
    
-   Automatic analysis of pull requests and branches with results reported inline
    
-   IDE Support with [SonarQube for IDE](https://www.sonarsource.com/products/sonarlint/) integration
    
-   Quality Gate (added as a GitHub check) acting at two different levels - first, preventing you from merging pull requests that contain issues - and later, helping you to release only clean, safe code
    
-   Sign up for SonarQube free tier and begin scanning your private and public repositories
    

A [GitHub Action](https://github.com/marketplace/actions/sonarcloud-scan) is available in the marketplace to make it easy for you (for projects where automatic analysis isn't available). SonarQube Cloud also integrates smoothly with Jenkins, CircleCI, TravisCI, CirrusCI, and many other tools.

A free tier is available that allows you to explore the benefits of SonarQube Cloud using your public and private repositories. We also provide a no-commitment, [14-day trial](https://www.sonarsource.com/products/sonarcloud/signup/) of SonarQube Cloud Team for unlimited team members, up to 1.9M LoC, AI CodeFix recommendations, and more. No need to speak with a sales rep or request a license key - get automatic code analysis results on your private projects in minutes! Want to see more examples of SonarCloud in action? You can [explore current Open Source projects in SonarCloud](https://sonarcloud.io/explore/projects?sort=-analysis_date) that are using the [Clean as You Code](https://www.sonarsource.com/solutions/our-unique-approach/) methodology.

What are you waiting for? SonarQube Cloud helps you consistently deliver cleaner, secure software that future developers will appreciate and your users will love. Start writing Clean Code. [Now](https://www.sonarsource.com/products/sonarcloud/signup/)!

pull_request.body:
# Proposed Changes

This PR adds an ingress to the web interface. It uses a template to update the baseurl so the panel can correctly handle requests. The port binding cannot be removed since it is used by tasmota devices to connect to the update server.
